# Repository Agent Instructions

- Work only inside this repository unless explicitly told otherwise.
- Before any edits, identify the run, test, and lint commands.
- Do not use destructive git commands without direct approval.
- Prefer the smallest useful patch over broad refactoring for narrow tasks.
- If behavior is unclear, reproduce the problem and form a root-cause hypothesis first.
- Do not change the public API without separate confirmation.
- When editing code, add or update the relevant test when possible.
- After changes, always list the modified files.
- After changes, always list the checks you ran.
- After changes, always list the remaining risks.
- If code, README, or config contradict this file, call out the conflict before proceeding.
